ke University Press|location=Durham, NC|isbn=978-0-8223-2870-4|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book|last1=Sriram|first1=Chandra Lekha|last2=Martin-Ortega|first2=Olga|last3=Herman|first3=Johanna|title=War, Conflict and Human rights: Theory and Practice|year=2010|publisher=Routledge|edition=|location=London, UK; New York, NY|isbn=978-0-415-45205-2|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book | first = Mark | last = Thompson | authorlink = Mark Thompson (historian) | title = Forging War: The Media in Serbia, Croatia and Bosnia-Hercegovina | others = International Centre Against Censorship, [[Article 19]] | year = 1994 | location = Avon, United Kingdom | publisher = The Bath Press | ref = harv}}\n*{{cite book|last=Wydra|first=Harald|title=Communism and the Emergence of Democracy|year=2007|publisher=Cambridge University Press|location=Cambridge, UK; New York, NY|isbn=978-0-521-85169-5|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book|last=Zimmermann|first=Warren|title=Origins of a Catastrophe: Yugoslavia and its Destroyers|year=1996|publisher=Times Books|edition=1st|location=New York, NY|isbn=978-0-8129-6399-1|ref=harv|url=https://archive.org/details/originsofcatastr00zimm}}\n{{Refend}}\n\n;News reports\n{{Refbegin|40em}}\n*{{cite news | ref = Eckholm08-10-2000 | newspaper = [[The New York Times]] | url = https://www.nytimes.com/2000/10/08/world/showdown-yugoslavia-ally-china-once-supporter-milosevic-against-nato-sends-its.html | title = Showdown in Yugoslavia: An Ally | last = Eckholm | first = Erik | date = 8 October 2000 | accessdate =22 October 2011 }}\n\n{{Refend}}\n\n==Further reading==\n{{Refbegin|40em}}\n*[https://www.webcitation.org/63jkkeI42?url=http://www.domovina.net/ Recorded telephone conversations of Slobodan Milo\u0161evi\u0107 as Yugoslav crisis unfolded (transcripts in English)]\n*{{Cite journal\n| last       = Clark\n| first      = Janine\n|date=May 2007\n| title      = National Minorities and the Milo\u0161evi\u0107 Regime\n| journal    = [[Nationalities Papers]]\n| volume     = 35\n| issue      = 2\n| pag